The paper deals with the problem of finding sparse spanners in dense graphs with temporal connectivity, which involves topics such as graph theory, data structures, and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the concept of cliques, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper mentions the extension of the results to more general models of temporal cliques, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
